title: Mouse Guard - Fall 1152, Winter 1152, Legends of the Guard (digi
description:
English | CBZ and CBR | 3 Issues

Mouse Guard - Fall 1152
Publisher:  Archaia Entertainment
Publication Date:  June 24, 2009

Story and Art by David Petersen

The fearless Mouse Guard are dispatched to find a missing merchant. Their search reveals much more than they expect, as they stumble across a traitor in the Guard's own ranks. The volume collects the first Mouse Guard series. Features an Epilogue and special bonus material!

Mouse Guard - Winter 1152
Publication Date:  July 22, 2009

Story and Art by David Petersen

In the Winter of 1152, the Guard face a food and supply shortage threatening the lives of many through a cold and icy season. Saxon, Kenzie, Lieam, and Sadie, led by Celanawe, traverse the snow-blanketed territories acting as diplomats to improve relations between the mouse cities and the Guard. This is a winter that not every Guard may survive! Collects the second Eisner-Award winnning series with an all-new epilogue and bonus content.

Mouse Guard - Legends of the Guard
Publication Date:  November 10, 2010

Writers:  Jeremy Bastian, Ted Naifeh, Alex Sheikman, Alex Kain, Terry Moore, Lowell Francis, Katie Cook, Guy Davis, Nate Pride, Jason Shawn Alexander, Craig Rousseau, Karl Kerschl, Mark Smylie
Artists:  Jeremy Bastian, Ted Naifeh, Alex Sheikman, Scott Keating, Sean Rubin, Terry Moore, Gene Ha, Katie Cook, Guy Davis, Nate Pride, Jason Shawn Alexander, Craig Rousseau, Karl Kerschl, Mark Smylie
Additional Pages:  David Peterson
Additional Lettering:  Dave Lanphear

A new Mouse Guard anthology series featuring the work of artists and storytellers handpicked by series creator David Petersen. Bonus content includes an all-new Epilogue illustrated by Joao Lemos (Avengers Fairy Tales), cover gallery, character lineup, floor plan of the June Alley Inn, and creator bios.

Thanks goes to Empire for this release.
